    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How do I calculate the home office deduction?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>Two methods: (1) Simplified: $5 per square foot, max 300 sq ft, max $1,500 deduction. (2) Regular: calculate the percentage of your home used for business (office sq ft ÷ total home sq ft), then apply that percentage to actual home expenses including rent, utilities, insurance, and depreciation. Use whichever method produces the larger deduction.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
